# Unified Public Navbar

When the user says **edit navbar**, **nav bar**, **header**, **top bar**, or **site nav**, treat it as a **site-wide** change on **every public page** — not a single route.

## Canonical implementation (do not fork per page)

| Piece | File | Role |
|-------|------|------|
| **PublicNavbar** | `components/layout/PublicNavbar.tsx` | Single entry — render this in layouts |
| **SiteNavLogoBar** | `components/layout/SiteNavLogoBar.tsx` | Centered Hathor ring logo (no BOOK NOW pills) |
| **Header** | `components/layout/Header.tsx` | Primary nav links + mobile explore + theme toggle |
| **Nav data** | `lib/public-nav.ts` | `HEADER_NAV_ITEMS`, `EXPLORE_LINKS` |
| **Nav styles** | `app/site-nav.css` | Logo bar + dropdown pill styles |

**Reference:** `/` is the home experience (former EX page). All public routes use the same `PublicLayout` → `PublicNavbar`.

## Rules

1. **Never** add page-local nav bars, duplicate headers, or route-specific BOOK NOW pills in the top tier.
2. **Never** reintroduce flanking gold BOOK NOW bars in the navbar — booking CTAs belong in page content or the booking modal trigger elsewhere, not the fixed top nav.
3. Layouts must use `<PublicNavbar />` only (`PublicLayout`, `app/preview/layout.tsx`). Do not wire `Header` / `SiteNavLogoBar` separately in new code.
4. Page layouts may set **theme/background** only on the home route shell — not alternate nav markup or nav-specific BOOK NOW UI.
5. Admin (`/admin/**`) and booking flows keep their own shells; this rule is for the public marketing site.

## When editing nav

- Change `lib/public-nav.ts` for links/labels.
- Change `Header.tsx` / `SiteNavLogoBar.tsx` / `site-nav.css` for structure and styling.
- Verify on **at least two routes** (e.g. `/` and `/cruises`) that the nav matches.
